results.description:
White Rock lake, Winfrey Point
Friendly Little Monks 
Two brave little parakeets left the group and flew over right by me and started eating acorns just a few feet in front of me.  One was too close for me to photograph it.
This is the closest I've ever been to these birds.  I was as still as I could be while slowly pushing the shutter.
Once the acorn was broken, it was crushing it with its foot. 
Absolutely beautiful birds.  Such a thrill to have them eat this close in my presence.
